<p>I work in commercial analytics for the pharmaceutical industry in Singapore, which mostly means reconciling data sources that describe the same reality and disagree about it. One system says the doctor was engaged. Another says the product didn't move. Deciding which number to trust, and being able to defend that decision in a room, is the actual job.</p>
<p>Rounding Errors is that job as a hobby. Countries publish numbers about themselves, other institutions publish different numbers about the same countries, and the gaps run to billions, occasionally an entire Greece. I collect the good ones.</p>
<p>Half the fun is the exhibits. The other half is seeing how far Claude and Claude Code can carry a one-person museum, currently: research, drafting, charts, and the entire deployment.</p>
<p>Views here are mine and not my employer's.</p>
